targets.rawSql: SELECT COALESCE(SUM(net_profit), 0) FROM manufacturing_pipelines WHERE status = 'COMPLETED' AND completed_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '1 hour'
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM manufacturing_pipelines WHERE status IN ('PLANNING', 'EXECUTING') AND pipeline_type = 'FABRICATION'

SELECT
    p.pipeline_type,
    p.product_good,
    p.status,
    p.sell_market,
    COALESCE(completed.cnt, 0)::float / NULLIF(total.cnt, 0)::float as progress,
    p.created_at
FROM manufacturing_pipelines p
LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
    SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM manufacturing_tasks t
    WHERE t.pipeline_id = p.id AND t.status = 'COMPLETED'
) completed ON true
LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
    SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM manufacturing_tasks t
    WHERE t.pipeline_id = p.id
) total ON true
WHERE p.status IN ('PLANNING', 'EXECUTING')
ORDER BY p.pipeline_type, p.created_at DESC
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM manufacturing_pipelines WHERE status IN ('PLANNING', 'EXECUTING') AND pipeline_type = 'COLLECTION'

SELECT
    t.assigned_ship as ship,
    t.task_type,
    t.good,
    t.status,
    COALESCE(t.factory_symbol, t.source_market) as source,
    t.target_market as destination,
    COALESCE(p.product_good, 'N/A') as pipeline_target,
    p.pipeline_type,
    EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.started_at))::int as running_sec
FROM manufacturing_tasks t
LEFT JOIN manufacturing_pipelines p ON t.pipeline_id = p.id
WHERE t.status IN ('ASSIGNED', 'EXECUTING')
  AND t.assigned_ship IS NOT NULL
  AND t.assigned_ship != ''
ORDER BY t.started_at DESC

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    t.good,
    COALESCE(t.source_market, t.factory_symbol) as source,
    CASE
        WHEN t.task_type = 'COLLECT_SELL' THEN 'N/A (factory)'
        WHEN t.good IN ('IRON_ORE','COPPER_ORE','ALUMINUM_ORE','PLATINUM_ORE','GOLD_ORE','SILVER_ORE','URANITE_ORE','MERITIUM_ORE','SILICON_CRYSTALS','QUARTZ_SAND','AMMONIA_ICE','LIQUID_HYDROGEN','LIQUID_NITROGEN','HYDROCARBON','DIAMONDS','PRECIOUS_STONES','ICE_WATER') THEN 'N/A (raw)'
        ELSE COALESCE((SELECT supply FROM market_data md WHERE md.waypoint_symbol = t.source_market AND md.good_symbol = t.good ORDER BY last_updated DESC LIMIT 1), 'UNKNOWN')
    END as source_supply,
    EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.created_at))::int as waiting_sec,
    t.task_type
FROM manufacturing_tasks t
WHERE t.status = 'PENDING'
ORDER BY t.created_at ASC
LIMIT 15

panels.title: ‚è≥ Pending (Supply-Gated)

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    COALESCE(p.product_good, 'N/A') as pipeline,
    t.good,
    t.priority as base_priority,
    t.priority + LEAST(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))/30, 100)::int as effective_priority,
    EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))::int as waiting,
    t.source_market as source,
    t.target_market as destination
FROM manufacturing_tasks t
LEFT JOIN manufacturing_pipelines p ON t.pipeline_id = p.id
WHERE t.status = 'READY' AND t.task_type = 'ACQUIRE_DELIVER'
ORDER BY
    t.priority + LEAST(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))/30, 100)::int DESC,
    t.ready_at ASC
LIMIT 15

SELECT
    COALESCE(p.product_good, 'N/A') as pipeline,
    t.good,
    t.priority as base_priority,
    t.priority + LEAST(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))/30, 100)::int as effective_priority,
    EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))::int as waiting_sec,
    t.factory_symbol as factory,
    t.target_market as destination
FROM manufacturing_tasks t
LEFT JOIN manufacturing_pipelines p ON t.pipeline_id = p.id
WHERE t.status = 'READY' AND t.task_type = 'COLLECT_SELL'
ORDER BY
    t.priority + LEAST(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - t.ready_at))/30, 100)::int DESC,
    t.ready_at ASC
LIMIT 15

SELECT
    f.output_good,
    f.factory_symbol,
    f.current_supply,
    f.ready_for_collection,
    COALESCE(p.product_good, 'N/A') as pipeline_target
FROM manufacturing_factory_states f
LEFT JOIN manufacturing_pipelines p ON f.pipeline_id = p.id
WHERE p.status = 'EXECUTING' OR p.status IS NULL
ORDER BY
    CASE f.current_supply
        WHEN 'SCARCE' THEN 1
        WHEN 'LIMITED' THEN 2
        WHEN 'MODERATE' THEN 3
        WHEN 'HIGH' THEN 4
        WHEN 'ABUNDANT' THEN 5
    END ASC
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM manufacturing_factory_states WHERE ready_for_collection = true

SELECT
    pipeline_type,
    product_good,
    net_profit,
    total_revenue,
    total_cost,
    completed_at
FROM manufacturing_pipelines
WHERE status = 'COMPLETED'
ORDER BY completed_at DESC
LIMIT 10
SELECT COALESCE(MAX(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (NOW() - ready_at))/60), 0) as max_wait FROM manufacturing_tasks WHERE status = 'READY'
